English:CategoryProgrammerUtils|
Français:CatégorieOutilsDuProgrammeur

Click on the header to list all pages on the wiki with information
related to programming utils.

Debugging tools are listed in CategoryDebug.

If you are looking for a interface to some external utility not
directly related to programming, see CategoryExternalUtilities
instead.

This is an attempt to collect tools that help programmers be more
productive in dealing with programs written in languages such as C,
C++, Java, etc.  I started this category initially to collect
information regarding code browsers.

This page list the utilities together with a short description.  If
more information is available, it should be moved to its own page.

See also: [[EmacsNiftyTricks#Programming]]

Examine code:

* JavaDevelopmentEnvironment -- Java程序员的百宝箱
** TexiDoclet -- 生成Info格式的Java文档
* ObjectOrientedBrowser -- 支持 C++, Java, Python以及其它少数几种语言
* EmacsBrowse -- 虽然要比ObjectOrientedBrowser简单, 但是集成在Emacs
* SpeedBar -- provides alternate views into individual source files
* EmacsCodeBrowser -- provides views of directories and files that go one step beyond what SpeedBar does
* ConnectedGraphEditor (COGRE) -- a base library for editing and manipulating connected graphs
* DoxyMacs -- 一个C和C++的文档系统
* CmodeAddons -- 编码的时候显示C函数的参数

源代码编辑:

* CodeBeautifying -- reindenting code and rewrapping comments.
* ElDoc -- shows you the argument list of functions in the echo area
* EdiffMode -- Interactively diffing, merging and patching.
* EmergeDiff -- graphical interface to "diff"
* ExpandMemberFunctions -- expand member functions from C++ header files into C++ source files
* RefactoringBrowser -- a proprietary refactoring browser for Emacs

Searching and indexing of source code:

* EmacsTags (etags) -- easy location of identifiers in source files based on a TagFile
** BuildTags -- more information on how to create these files
* ExuberantCtags (ctags) -- supports more languages and editors than etags
* CScopeAndEmacs -- quickly lookup where a symbol is defined, where it is called, etc.
* IdUtils -- Database of code identifiers

Misc:

* SmartCompile -- better `compile'
* ModeCompile -- another better `compile'
* FlyMake -- run make on the fly, highlight errors/warnings in source buffer
* MajorComint -- a snippet to associate a particular major mode with a comint subprocess.
* AsciiTable -- a simple ASCII table command
* AsciiMode -- 显示ASCII编码.
* PrettyLambda -- a way to use a lambda character in scheme-mode
* CollectionOfEmacsDevelopmentEnvironmentTools (CEDET) -- most of
  these tools have their own pages

Cette page est aussi disponible en français: Français:CatégorieOutilsDuProgrammeur


